      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RIVERCREST MAGIC (10) has been a touch disappointing since winning over the mile three starts ago. Back to 1300m today, but she was solid here two back and should sit much closer today than she did there. Remains down in the weights and can return to winning ways. SCOTTISH LAIRD (1) is knocking on the door of another victory, just missing as the race favourite over 1400m last time out when on the quick turnaround. He jumped the favourite there and this looks well placed from the inside barrier. Faithfull sticks and he can go one better. HIGH PRECISION (2) bolted in over 1100m two back and never got into the race last start when racing over 1200m. Out to 1300m now, but she's a winner at this track and trip previously. Can bounce back in a big way. RUNFORROB (7) is right back in trip now but can feature if he holds his form. PENNED (9) was much better last start and can't be discounted.",
